 A medical professional and a Senior Lecturer in the Department of Public Health, Faculty of Medicine and Surgery, Imo State University, Owerri , Dr. Ijeomah Linus Arodiogbu, yesterday said  he has  advantage to emerge South-east zonal chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC). The medical practitioner, indicated   interest to run for the position of the South-east Zonal Chairman of the APC, in an expression of interest  form he  sent to  Extraordinary Planning Committee of the party. The 53-year old Arodiogbu, who hails from Arondizuogu in the Ideato North Local Government Area (LGA) of Imo State, said he has consulted widely for the position and  convinced he has the full support and approval of key APC stakeholders in his state. Arodiogbu said he is duly qualified for the position, stressing: “ I am a registered member of the APC from Arondizuogu Ward 1, Idea to North LGA, Imo State”. In 2021, he was the Secretary, Appeal Committee, Anambra State Governorship Primary. He was also the Chairman, APC Congress; Ward Congress, Enugu State, Chairman, APC Congress; LGA Congress, Enugu State, Chairman, APC Congress State Congress, Enugu State, Member, Convention Planning Subcommittee, and Accommodation Subcommittee among other assignments which he approached diligently to the best of expectations, and delivering quality services to the satisfaction of the Party’s National Office.